{'relation': ['https://d-scholarship.pitt.edu/48476/', 'https://cesf.pitt.edu'], 'title': ['Community partner compensation: strategies for humanizing payment processes'], 'creator': ['Savage Friedman, Felicia', 'Snider, Amy'], 'description': ['Equitable compensation for people’s time and contributions is one way to demonstrate respect, dignity, and trustworthiness in the context of engaged scholarship. Institutional processes including contracts and payment processes can be challenging for individuals to navigate.  \r\n\r\nThis workshop will share workflows for contracts, invoicing, and payment processes that involve increased transparency and accountability. The workflows consider approaching these institutional processes with several key questions: What are ways for those of us within academic institutions to reduce administrative burden for community partners? And how can we work collaboratively across our internal systems to expedite contracting and payment processes? Together, we can humanize our institutional processes on the pathway to strengthening our community partnerships.'], 'date': ['2025-03-04'], 'type': ['Conference or Workshop Item', 'PeerReviewed'], 'format': ['application/vnd.ms-powerpoint', 'application/pdf'], 'language': ['en', 'en'], 'rights': [None, None], 'identifier': ['https://d-scholarship.pitt.edu/48476/1/Snider_Humanizing%20Institutional%20Processes_FINAL_20250304_FeliciaSavageFriedman.pptx', 'https://d-scholarship.pitt.edu/48476/2/Snider_Humanizing%20Institutional%20Processes_FINAL_20250304_FeliciaSavageFriedman.pdf', '  Savage Friedman, Felicia and Snider, Amy  (2025) Community partner compensation: strategies for humanizing payment processes.  In: 2025 Community Engaged Scholarship Forum, 2025-03-04, University of Pittsburgh.    (Unpublished)  ']}